<title>CANADA: Asian forum condemns Peru hostage crisis.</title>
<headline>Asian forum condemns Peru hostage crisis.</headline>
<dateline>VANCOUVER, British Columbia 1997-01-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Parliamentarians from Pacific Rim countries on Wednesday called on Peruvian rebels to release the 74 hostages being held at the Japanese ambassador's residence in Lima.</p>
<p>The Asia Pacific Parliamentary Forum, which groups legislators from 25 countries, approved a resolution submitted jointly by Japan and Peru during its annual meeting, a spokeswoman said.</p>
<p>The resolution condemned the three-week-old hostage crisis and urged the Peruvian government &quot;not to bargain with terrorists,&quot; she said. Marxist rebels stormed the Japanese ambassador's residence in Lima Dec. 17, demanding the release of 400 jailed comrades.</p>
<p>Participating in the four-day Vancouver meeting are legislators from Australia, Brunei, Cambodia, Canada, Chile, China, Fiji, Indonesia, Japan, South Korea, Laos, Malaysia, Marshall Islands, Mexico, Micronesia, Mongolia, New Zealand, Papua New Guinea, Peru, the Philippines, Russia, Singapore, Thailand, the United States and Vietnam.</p>
